#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NotesCVS_RSH.
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

You can use CVS with RSH if you have the rsh-sever installed.

Put the following in the ".bashrc" file:
	export CVS_RSH=rsh

RedHat 7.3 and 8.0 disk 2 has the rsh-server.

Use "rpm -i" to intall the rsh-server.

Go to /etc/xinetd.d/rsh file and change "disable = yes" to "disable = no"

Reboot or restart xinetd.  "/usr/bin/redhat-config-services"

You need to have a ".rhosts" file in the target user directory.

You need to have ".rhosts" file permissions set so that others "o" do not have write permission.

Example .rhosts file:

	10.0.1.140 bergman
	10.0.1.141 bergman
	10.0.1.142 bergman
	10.0.1.143 bergman
	10.0.1.144 bergman
	10.0.1.145 bergman

Look at /var/log/messages for helpful info.


You can use CVS with SSH if you have the sshd server installed.

Put the following in the ".bashrc" file:
        export CVS_RSH=ssh

You will have to type a password unless you get the ssh-agent going.

If there are problems check the /var/log files!!!!

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Importing.
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
     cd /home/steswd/steswd
     cvs import -m "New Version of STESWD." steswd200305A ITT start

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Exporting.
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
     cvs export -D today ene001
     cvs export -D today bfg001

# Export
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
cvs -d "steswd@10.103.53.101:/basestation/ittcvs" export -D now bdw200607A  bfg200607A  bms200607A  ged200607A  rds200607A  sdds200607A  spg200607A  steswd200607A  xmc200607A

# Check out
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
cvs -d "steswd@10.103.53.101:/basestation/ittcvs" checkout bdw200607A  bfg200607A  bms200607A  ged200607A  rds200607A  sdds200607A  spg200607A  steswd200607A  xmc200607A

# Compare checked out version with repository on local machine.
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# While in directory with checkout code.
cvs -qn update

# Compare checked out version with repository on remote machine.
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# While in directory with checkout code.
cvs -d "steswd@10.103.53.101:/basestation/ittcvs" -qn update

# Commit changes on local machine.
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# While in directory with checkout code.
cvs commit -m "Updates."

# Commit changes on remote machine.
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# While in directory with checkout code.
cvs -d "steswd@10.103.53.101:/basestation/ittcvs" commit -m "Updates."
